{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774313236,"nonce":"RzErAJB8oS/vLB/2kny2FsMK+LM=","title":"Part 2.5 experiment: loss function + training objective comparison runs","message":"## Objective\n\nTrain PAI-ASF models with different loss configurations and training objectives to determine:\n1. Does a running cost (constant position error from go cue) produce peak velocity increases at high SISU?\n2. Does reviving the softmin goal-hit-window produce this effect?\n3. Do CVaR or APT training objectives add further H-infinity-like behavioral signatures?\n\n## Training Conditions\n\nAll conditions use PAI-ASF, gusts (n_expected=3, duration_mean=8, std=1.0), 5 replicates, 10k batches.\n\n### Loss variants (standard backprop):\n1. Running cost: constant-weight effector_pos from go cue, reduced late penalty\n2. Softmin: revived goal-hit-window (bug fixed), strong weight\n3. Combined: weak running cost + strong softmin\n\n### Training objectives (best loss from above):\n4. CVaR 10%\n5. APT (3 inner steps)\n\n### Control:\n6. No-perturbation baseline (pert std = 0)\n\ntarget_ratio: start with 0.3, also do 0.5\n\n## Evaluation\n\n- Peak velocity distributions: SISU=0 vs SISU=1, no eval perturbations\n- Max lateral deviation vs SISU under fixed gust\n- Feedback gain curves vs SISU\n- Loss curves across training iterations\n\n## Infrastructure\n\nTPU v5litepod-1, europe-west4-b (TRC, free). Feature branch from eager-models-migration.\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}